From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: MeshCore Security Audit <audit@meshcore.local>
Date: Wed, 23 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] bug22: Suspend radio during all flash write operations

The original bug22 fix only suspended the radio around acl.save().
Every "set" CLI command also calls savePrefs() which does flash I/O
(remove + write + close) with the radio fully active. Users currently
work around this by disabling repeat mode before changing settings.

This patch:
1. Adds Radio::suspendRadio() — puts the radio into standby via idle()
2. Wraps savePrefs() and saveRegions() callbacks in all three variants
   (repeater, room_server, sensor) with suspendRadio() before flash I/O

After this patch, users no longer need to disable repeat mode before
running set commands. The radio is put into standby for the duration of
the flash write (~10-100ms depending on page operations), then
automatically restarts on the next recvRaw() call in the main loop.

This is self-contained and does NOT depend on the earlier
bug22-flash-hang.patch (which only guarded acl.save() with deferral
logic). This patch takes a simpler approach: unconditionally suspend
before write, unconditionally resume after.
---
 examples/simple_repeater/MyMesh.h    | 10 ++++++++--
 examples/simple_room_server/MyMesh.h | 10 ++++++++--
 examples/simple_sensor/SensorMesh.h  |  8 +++++++-
 src/Dispatcher.h                     |  7 +++++++
 src/helpers/radiolib/RadioLibWrappers.h |  1 +
 5 files changed, 31 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/Dispatcher.h b/src/Dispatcher.h
index 0000001..0000002 100644
--- a/src/Dispatcher.h
+++ b/src/Dispatcher.h
@@ -70,6 +70,13 @@ public:
 
   virtual bool isInRecvMode() const = 0;
 
+  /**
+   * \brief  Put radio into standby. Next recvRaw() call will restart receive.
+   *         Used to quiesce the SPI bus before flash I/O on nRF52, and to
+   *         prevent radio interrupts during NVMC page erase/write.
+  */
+  virtual void suspendRadio() { }
+
   /**
    * \returns  true if the radio is currently mid-receive of a packet.
   */
diff --git a/src/helpers/radiolib/RadioLibWrappers.h b/src/helpers/radiolib/RadioLibWrappers.h
index 0000001..0000002 100644
--- a/src/helpers/radiolib/RadioLibWrappers.h
+++ b/src/helpers/radiolib/RadioLibWrappers.h
@@ -31,6 +31,7 @@ public:
   bool isSendComplete() override;
   void onSendFinished() override;
   bool isInRecvMode() const override;
+  void suspendRadio() override { idle(); }
   bool isChannelActive();
 
   bool isReceiving() override { 
diff --git a/examples/simple_repeater/MyMesh.h b/examples/simple_repeater/MyMesh.h
index 0000001..0000002 100644
--- a/examples/simple_repeater/MyMesh.h
+++ b/examples/simple_repeater/MyMesh.h
@@ -191,8 +191,12 @@ public:
 
   void savePrefs() override {
+    _radio->suspendRadio();
     _cli.savePrefs(_fs);
   }
 
+  bool saveRegions() override;
 
diff --git a/examples/simple_repeater/MyMesh.cpp b/examples/simple_repeater/MyMesh.cpp
index 0000001..0000002 100644
--- a/examples/simple_repeater/MyMesh.cpp
+++ b/examples/simple_repeater/MyMesh.cpp
@@ -1124,7 +1124,9 @@ void MyMesh::handleSensorData(uint8_t type, const uint8_t* data, size_t len) {
 }
 
 bool MyMesh::saveRegions() {
+  _radio->suspendRadio();
   return region_map.save(_fs);
 }
 
diff --git a/examples/simple_room_server/MyMesh.h b/examples/simple_room_server/MyMesh.h
index 0000001..0000002 100644
--- a/examples/simple_room_server/MyMesh.h
+++ b/examples/simple_room_server/MyMesh.h
@@ -185,8 +185,12 @@ public:
 
   void savePrefs() override {
+    _radio->suspendRadio();
     _cli.savePrefs(_fs);
   }
 
diff --git a/examples/simple_sensor/SensorMesh.h b/examples/simple_sensor/SensorMesh.h
index 0000001..0000002 100644
--- a/examples/simple_sensor/SensorMesh.h
+++ b/examples/simple_sensor/SensorMesh.h
@@ -62,7 +62,13 @@ public:
-  void savePrefs() override { _cli.savePrefs(_fs); }
+  void savePrefs() override {
+    _radio->suspendRadio();
+    _cli.savePrefs(_fs);
+  }
   bool formatFileSystem() override;
